<section>
  <h3>Order of values in shorthand properties</h3>
  <p>Shorthand properties like <code>padding</code> and <code>margin</code>
  behave differently for different numbers of arguments.<p>
<pre>
padding: 30px;                    # top/bottom/left/right: 30px 
padding: 30px 15px;               # top/bottom: 30px left/right: 15px
padding: 30px 15px 20px;          # top: 30px left/right: 15px bottom: 20px
padding: 30px 15px 12px 20px;     # top: 30px right: 15px bottom: 12px left: 20px
</pre>
<p>So, the syntax is basically:</p>
<pre>
padding: all;
padding: top/bottom left/right;
padding: top left/right bottom;
padding: top left bottom right;
</pre>
</section>
